      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements under ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are primary indicators of implant structural adequacy under physiological loading. Force at 40 mm displacement is the ASTM F1717 reporting endpoint used by FDA reviewers. All three QoIs are directly relevant to the COU. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
