    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is judged acceptable given the large experimental sample size (N=11), inter-laboratory replication, and tight QoI agreement across all three output metrics (maximum E/uval 1.03, maximum percent difference 2.4%). Overall credibility is sufficient to support regulatory use of the FEA framework for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
